snippet.textDisplay: From what I understand, I think this song is an ode to and honours the classic Pakistani film industry, primarily Punjabi film industry. There was a trend back in the day of families gathering for an open space movie night, the drive-in movie theater under the open skies. Those were the good days when families would feel safe to sit in their cars or have a picnic at the drive-in cinemas. That last shot with credits displaying on the projector reminded me of Punjabi movies at drive-in. Movies of Sultan Rahi, Neelo Begum and so many others
